<subSubSection id="809506DD659346DFEFF67C7DA30BA1E8" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="notes">
<paragraph id="50D42BB6C9B57E5F7E4EBFBD144692C7" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EC7D59FDFCF809F77437760D9A685981" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
In describing 
<taxonomicName id="FE602BC54B38D6042BDCC7F4DE51C0D8" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1860" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium chaetocalyx" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chaetocalyx">
<emphasis id="55B4A61FA5E9B8AC010B4E11BCB9B273" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Eritrichium chaetocalyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="B47AC7C046B89377F8E1FD45DC964728" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.162865" author="Philippi, RA" journalOrPublisher="INTA, Buenos Aires" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" refId="B35" refString="Philippi, RA, 1860. Florula Atacamensis seu enumeratio plantarum, quas in itinere per desertum Atacamense. Sumptibus E. Anton. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.162865" title="Florula Atacamensis seu enumeratio plantarum, quas in itinere per desertum Atacamense. Sumptibus E. Anton." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.162865" year="1860">Rudolph A. Philippi (1860)</bibRefCitation>
cited a gathering he made near Pan de 
<normalizedToken id="889C9AC0D81DEDA1F5821CCD0B8E32E1" originalValue="Azúcar">Azucar</normalizedToken>
, Chile. Two duplicates of the type collection in agreement with the protologue and annotated by him as &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="6DA8B34DB0E7CEEE52E21EC6E9A2DF21" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1860" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium chaetocalyx" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chaetocalyx">Eritrichium chaetocalyx</taxonomicName>
&quot; were located at SGO. 
<bibRefCitation id="2A50F31A9B5E38DCD142FEE4011E04CD" author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">Johnston (1927)</bibRefCitation>
discussed this name and its original material, referring to a sheet lodged at SGO as the 
<normalizedToken id="03A00E9D183121F1638F51AD94F2747F" originalValue="“type”">&quot;type&quot;</normalizedToken>
of the name. In this context, 
<bibRefCitation id="A92D2470D8E07148EC77BBABD556B840" author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">
<normalizedToken id="700C73B1E6D933B88719E8E7BAD67ADB" originalValue="Johnston’s">Johnston's</normalizedToken>
(1927)
</bibRefCitation>
statement must thus be considered as a first-step typification. Thus, in order to narrow this designation, the sheet SGO000004073 is here selected as a second-step lectotype.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6F569ABB94709EFFE786F1544A58284D" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
In the protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="FEF5B144BD8174DC888215F2395E3B7B" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1895" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium divaricatum" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="divaricatum">
<emphasis id="BB24D728D1CA1B50B351F419831CF5A4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Eritrichium divaricatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="B4FD3C8678AEC4577453F380AAAA9138" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5354/0717-8883.2012.20872" author="Philippi, RA" journalOrPublisher="Anales de la Universidad de Chile" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="511 - 566" refId="B39" refString="Philippi, RA, 1895. Plantas nuevas chilenas de las familias que corresponden al tomo IV de la obra de Gay: (continuacion). Anales de la Universidad de Chile 90: 511 - 566, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5354/0717-8883.2012.20872" title="Plantas nuevas chilenas de las familias que corresponden al tomo IV de la obra de Gay: (continuacion)." url="https://doi.org/10.5354/0717-8883.2012.20872" volume="90" year="1895">Rudolph A. Philippi (1895)</bibRefCitation>
cited as type material a collection made by F. Philippi in Caldera, Chile. 
<bibRefCitation id="1719A118FEE139498EFB397EE7788000" author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">Johnston (1927)</bibRefCitation>
referred to a specimen kept at SGO as the 
<normalizedToken id="57257B15E33E9F23E7F15D3415B00852" originalValue="“type”">&quot;type&quot;</normalizedToken>
of the name, although two sheets annotated, in R. A. 
<normalizedToken id="9402BF5324447E37B383D2D89180E82B" originalValue="Philippi’s">Philippi's</normalizedToken>
hand, as &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="32B6A3FE7A564A78F0D108F4F3B7CEBB" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1895" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium divaricatum" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="divaricatum">Eritrichium divaricatum</taxonomicName>
&quot; are found there. This situation determines that 
<bibRefCitation id="B3DCCD9189A98CB2BCA7B69DD4165F71" author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">
<normalizedToken id="D1262B923AE1C19DE4FD4EC41438FCA3" originalValue="Johnston’s">Johnston's</normalizedToken>
(1927)
</bibRefCitation>
statement must be considered as a first-step lectotypification. In this context, the duplicate SGO000004070 is here selected as a second-step lectotype (Art. 9.17 of the ICN; 
<bibRefCitation id="B04EF1B9E1AB469E6BE830E2189EFF39" DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" author="Turland, NJ" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" refId="B51" refString="Turland, NJ, Wiersema, JH, Barrie, FR, Greuter, W, Hawksworth, DL, Herendeen, PS, Knapp, S, Kusber, WH, Li, DZ, Marhold, K, May, TW, McNeill, J, Monro, AM, Prad, J, Price, MJ, Smith, GF, 2018. International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten. https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten." url="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" year="2018">Turland et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="27FB43709208DF9B1AF485EDF09E72E7" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
<bibRefCitation id="E87873E6C29CD2C6903A94B2A1B956C8" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5354/0717-8883.2012.20872" author="Philippi, RA" journalOrPublisher="Anales de la Universidad de Chile" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="511 - 566" refId="B39" refString="Philippi, RA, 1895. Plantas nuevas chilenas de las familias que corresponden al tomo IV de la obra de Gay: (continuacion). Anales de la Universidad de Chile 90: 511 - 566, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5354/0717-8883.2012.20872" title="Plantas nuevas chilenas de las familias que corresponden al tomo IV de la obra de Gay: (continuacion)." url="https://doi.org/10.5354/0717-8883.2012.20872" volume="90" year="1895">Rudolph A. Philippi (1895)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="3DCE8BE4C91E182BA2F7016862BEB363" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium pustulosum" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pustulosum">
